reviews.review: Whether one is a die-hard fan or a casual one, this film is a must see for anyone who has a connection to Star Wars. It has incredibly fun and fast-paced action from the opening crawl to the end credits. Even if there are things with the plot that arenâ€™t hashed out in the most expository detail, it is the most thrilling Star Wars film of the Disney era. Overall, the performances are great, and the force has never felt more epic.
I want to give it 5 stars, but i can't bring myself to. It was a really great movie but the substance was lacking
I started reading the critic reviews - so I was nervous going in... But I thought it was fun and a satisfying conclusion to the saga.
walked out a changed is all I have to say truly amazing experience once again! will definitely be going to see again!!

Been a fan since going to a double feature of Empire and Jedi when I was 8 years old. Empire is still my favorite but this one is a very close second. Really worth seeing.  Gonna see it again very soon.

I loved the movie and I think that JJ did the best that anyone could do with what he was handed back. Still with Luke had more collective screen time and this movie should have been 30 minutes longer.

Can't really say it better than what's already being said. But, I'll say that at least with Force Awakens they really had something. A defected stormtrooper, a wonderful force inspired woman, and a mysterious dark villian. What did they do with all of that? Instead we get something way out of left field. I even liked most of TLJ despite its major flaws. I should have known it was all downhill from there. At least we are at rock bottom and it can only go up from here.
Great movie! Wraps up the story very well!

A big criticism of this series is that they had no plan. But George Lucas didn't have a plan for Episodes IV thru VI... he had an outline. But obviously the Luke and Leia as brother and sister was created AFTER Empire Strikes Back. But that's kind of what makes them work, the fact that they weren't precisely planned out. That's their legacy. The prequels on the contrary were meticulously planned out, and I think that's why they didn't work. The OT will never be equaled. But I feel this trilogy did a good job at coming close and after time goes by, the kids who got to see these movies in theaters will love them all.
